des:
The North 103.3 FM - WDSE (formerly KUMD Duluth Public Radio) is a non-profit public radio station in Duluth, Minnesota providing independent alternative music, insightful local interviews and distinguished public affairs coverage. The North 103.3 has proudly served as the Northland's alternative media source since 1956. Duluth's first public FM radio station, The North 103.3 features an ever-growing lineup of locally crafted programs and a wide variety of music you simply can't find anywhere else.

With strong local and worldwide following as one of nation's premiere music tastemakers, The North 103.3 explores the spectrum of new music and old favorites in Indie Rock, Alternative Rock, Folk, Blues, Soul, Reggae, Jazz and much more!
